        height: 254.875
        xPosition: -2798.7754
        yPosition: -2423.0046
        items:
        - rid: 4538204734669717504
        - rid: 4538204734669717505
        - rid: 4538204734669717506
        characterName: Walter
        icon: 
    - rid: 4538204734068884448
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Good morning, sir, I came from Ellam because I heard that the village
          elder has gone missing.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884449
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Welcome in "The Nasty Scream"! First time in Satbury?
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884450
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Actually yes, I've never been to this part of Lunaris.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884451
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: How can I help you, sir?
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884452
      type: {class: OptionItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Tell me something about your chief missing. Do you know anything?
    - rid: 4538204734068884453
      type: {class: OptionItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Any rumours
    - rid: 4538204734068884454
      type: {class: OptionItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Good bye!
    - rid: 4538204734068884455
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Rolf needs help. He has problem with weeds or something. He lives next
          to farm field.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884456
      type: {class: RandomItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Flow, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data: 
    - rid: 4538204734068884457
      type: {class: RandomItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Flow, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data: 
    - rid: 4538204734068884458
      type: {class: RandomItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Flow, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data: 
    - rid: 4538204734068884459
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: I will have shop here, but it's in development right now.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884460
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Meredith is looking for her husband. He is missing like our chief.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884461
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Well, all I know is that he was stealing from me.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884462
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: He started with food, which he said he would pay for later.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884463
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: He even stole my fireplace fuel.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884464
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: But he's a good guy. I suspect someone was blackmailing him. I could
          see it in his eyes.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884465
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Even Kael'nor the Sleepless sent me a vision in which I saw him talking
          to a hooded person and handing him a bag.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884466
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: So if he was justified by a deity, I don't blame him.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884467
      type: {class: OptionItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Maybe he was actually guided by the hand of God to protect you.
    - rid: 4538204734068884468
      type: {class: OptionItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: But he stole from his own people! The people he was supposed to be
          protecting. How can a deity justify this?
    - rid: 4538204734068884469
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: I'm not saying it didn't, but look, maybe thanks to this we survived
          the winter without any deaths.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884470
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: No one in the village starved.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884471
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: We also managed with fuel.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884472
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: And the vision itself might be a gift from God to Hendrik, for doing
          everything he could for his people? We don't know what the gods' plans
          are.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884473
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: And you, do you think you are here of your own free will, or did Kareth,
          Erel or Kelvor send you here?
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884474
      type: {class: OptionItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Maybe you're right. Maybe it's no coincidence that I found the ad in
          Ellam.
    - rid: 4538204734068884475
      type: {class: OptionItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: I came here of my own free will
    - rid: 4538204734068884476
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Exactly! Maybe it was a coincidence... Or maybe not?
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884477
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: What is self-will? If I now act "according to my will," how can I be
          sure it wasn't planned?
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884478
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Anyway, sorry to interrupt but you have other things to do than argue
          with an old grump.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734068884479
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: If you manage to find the mayor and settle your affairs, come back
          to me, I will be happy to continue this conversation.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734669717504
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Exactly! Maybe it was a coincidence... Or maybe not?
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734669717505
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Perhaps Asha the Blooming wanted to help life in our village, or perhaps
          Velra the Shadowed one tricked him?
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 4538204734669717506
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Maybe we'll find out from him himself when you find him, who knows.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
--- !u!114 &3244058937086114821
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: e5800231a05eaae43b00503881229245, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  originalLanguage: en
  translationSets:
  - counter: 37
    languageCode: en
    translations:
    - id: 0
      language: en
      text: Player
    - id: 1
      language: en
      text: Good morning sir, I came from the continent because I heard that you
        have problems in the city. Who's in charge here?
    - id: 2
      language: en
      text: Bartender
    - id: 3
      language: en
      text: Welcome to my inn! First time in Moonveil?
    - id: 4
      language: en
      text: Actually yes, I've never been to this part of Lunaris.
    - id: 5
      language: en
      text: How can I help you, sir?
    - id: 6
      language: en
      text: Good morning, sir, I came from Ellam because I heard that the village
        elder has gone missing.
    - id: 7
      language: en
      text: Welcome in "The Nasty Scream"! First time in Satbury?
    - id: 8
      language: en
      text: Tell me something about your chief missing. Do you know anything?
    - id: 9
      language: en
      text: Any rumours
    - id: 10
      language: en
      text: Good bye!
    - id: 11
      language: en
      text: Rolf needs help. He has problem with weeds or something. He lives next
        to farm field.
    - id: 12
      language: en
      text: I will have shop here, but it's in development right now.
    - id: 13
      language: en
      text: Meredith is looking for her husband. He is missing like our chief.
    - id: 14
      language: en
      text: Well, all I know is that he was stealing from me.
    - id: 15
      language: en
      text: He started with food, which he said he would pay for later.
    - id: 16
      language: en
      text: He even stole my fireplace fuel.
    - id: 17
      language: en
      text: But he's a good guy. I suspect someone was blackmailing him. I could
        see it in his eyes.
    - id: 18
      language: en
      text: Even Kael'nor the sleepless sent me a vision in which I saw him talking
        to a hooded person and handing him a bag.
    - id: 19
      language: en
      text: So if he was justified by a deity, I don't blame him.
    - id: 20
      language: en
      text: But he stole from his own people! The people he was supposed to be protecting.
        How can a deity justify this?
    - id: 21
      language: en
      text: I'm not saying it didn't, but look, maybe thanks to this we survived
        the winter without any deaths.
    - id: 22
      language: en
      text: No one in the village starved.
    - id: 23
      language: en
      text: We also managed with fuel.
    - id: 24
      language: en
      text: And the vision itself might be a gift from God to Hendrik, for doing
        everything he could for his people? We don't know what the gods' plans are.
    - id: 25
      language: en
      text: And you, do you think you are here of your own free will, or did Kareth,
        Erel or Kelvor send you here?
    - id: 26
      language: en
      text: I came here of my own free will
    - id: 27
      language: en
      text: Maybe you're right. Maybe it's no coincidence that I found the ad in
        Ellam.
    - id: 28
      language: en
      text: Exactly! Maybe it was a coincidence... Or maybe not?
    - id: 29
      language: en
      text: What is self-will? If I now act "according to my will," how can I be
        sure it wasn't planned?
    - id: 30
      language: en
      text: Anyway, sorry to interrupt but you have other things to do than argue
        with an old grump.
    - id: 31
      language: en
      text: If you manage to find the mayor and settle your affairs, come back to
        me, I will be happy to continue this conversation.
    - id: 32
      language: en
      text: Maybe he was actually guided by the hand of God to protect you.
    - id: 33
      language: en
      text: Perhaps Asha the Blooming wanted to help life in our village, or perhaps
        Velra the Shadowed one tricked him?
    - id: 34
      language: en
      text: Maybe we'll find out from him himself when you find him, who knows.
    - id: 35
      language: en
      text: Walter
    - id: 36
      language: en
      text: Even Kael'nor the Sleepless sent me a vision in which I saw him talking
        to a hooded person and handing him a bag.
